<Entity class="oracle.dbtools.crest.model.design.logical.Entity" directorySegmentName="seg_6" id="5F9389BD-1C3F-2C71-4DF3-6222586FF434" name="General interest rate risk (GIRR) factor for standardised approach">
<createdBy>bosarie</createdBy>
<createdTime>2023-06-19 15:06:15 UTC</createdTime>
<commentInRDBMS><![CDATA[The General Interest Rate Risk (GIRR) factor refers to the sensitivity of financial instruments to changes in risk-free interest rates across different maturities and currencies. These include risks from inflation and cross-currency basis spreads. (Article 325l) - Regulation (EU) No 575/2013 of the European Parliament and of the Council (CRR)]]></commentInRDBMS>
